  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Slope Stabilization and Agriculture in Pohnpei, Federated States of Micronesia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project seeks to address food insecurity and agricultural damages caused by Tropical Storm Jelawat in March 2018 in Micronesia. The project is implementing an e-voucher system for affected households to restore and replant their destroyed lands in order to stabilize the affected land and re-planting appropriate agroforestry to prevent further soil erosion and future landslides and restore livelihoods and food security for affected households. In addition, IOM provides technical assistance and capacity building to local farmers on slope stabilization and watershed management techniques, to ensure agricultural restoration activities support disaster risk reduction and mitigate the impact of disasters.</narrative>
  </description>
